 are implemented, with often complex results, in countries throughout the region. Ultimately, Degrees of Dignity calls on the field of higher education development to rethink current approaches to higher education reform: rather than viewing the Arab world as a site for intervention, it argues that the Arab world can act as a source for insight on resilient higher education systems.  afunded by University of Toronto Libraries  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aThis eBook is made available Open Access under a CC BY-NC-ND 4.0 license: uhttps://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-nc-nd/4.0  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 26. Apr 2024) 0aArabsxEducation (Higher). 0aEducation, HigherzArab countries. 0aHigher education and statezArab countries. 7aEDUCATION / Higher.2bisacsh  aArab higher education.  aMiddle East.  aNational university.  aNorth Africa.  ahigher education in North Africa.  ahigher education in the Middle East.  aprivate university.2 aUniversity of Toronto Librariesefunder.4fnd4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/fnd08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertACUP Complete eBook-Package 2021z978311127221408iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2021 Englishz978311075400108iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2021z9783110753776oZDB-23-DGG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Sociology 2021 Englishz978311075418608iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Sociology 2021z9783110753967oZDB-23-DSL08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUniversity of Toronto Press Complete eBook-Package 2021z978311073922040uhttps://doi.org/10.3138/9781487546700zOpen Access7040uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781487546700zOpen Access70423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781487546700/origin